Class PasswordDictionaryRule

All Implemented Interfaces:
PasswordRule
public class PasswordDictionaryRule
extends AbstractPasswordRule

PasswordDictionaryRule contains methods for determining if a password contains a dictionary word of a specified length, forwards or backwards.

public PasswordDictionaryRule(edu.vt.middleware.dictionary.Dictionary dict)
This creates a new PasswordDictionaryRule with the supplied dictionary. The dictionary should be ready to use when passed to this constructor. Dictionary.build() should be called prior to passing the object to this constructor.

PasswordDictionaryRule

public PasswordDictionaryRule(edu.vt.middleware.dictionary.Dictionary dict,
                              int n)
This will create a new PasswordDictionaryRule with the supplied dictionary and number of characters. The dictionary should be ready to use when passed to this constructor. Dictionary.build() should be called prior to passing the object to this constructor. See setNumberOfCharacters(int).

Parameters:
dict - Dictionary to use for searching
n - int number of characters to check in each dictionary word
Method Detail

setNumberOfCharacters

public void setNumberOfCharacters(int n)
This will set the number of characters that constitute a word in a password. So if n = 5 and the password contains 'test', then the password is valid. However if n = 4 then 'test' will be found in the dictionary. The default number is 1.

Parameters:
n - int number of characters to check in each dictionary word

matchBackwards

public void matchBackwards()
This causes the verify method to search the password for dictionary words spelled backwards as well as forwards.

getMatchingWord

public java.lang.String getMatchingWord()
This returns the dictionary word which caused the password to fail. If no failure occured this value will be null.

Returns:
